#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:514
msgid ""
"To guess the sex, we have an true idea (example: female) and we obtain a "
"result with a method (example: using an api, querying a dataset or with a "
"machine learning model). The guessed result could be male, female or perhaps "
"unknown. To remember some definitions about results about this matter:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:517
msgid ""
"@strong{True positive} is to find a value guessed as true if the value in "
"the data source is positive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:520
msgid ""
"@strong{True negative} is to find a value guessed as true if the the value "
"in the data source is negative."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:523
msgid ""
"@strong{False positive} is to find a value guessed as false if the the value "
"in the data source is positive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:526
msgid ""
"@strong{False negative} is to find a value guessed as false if the the value "
"in the data source is negative."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:530
msgid ""
"So, we can find a vocabulary for measure true, false, success and errors. We "
"can make a summary in the gender name context about mathematical concepts:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:533
msgid ""
"@strong{Precision} is about true positives divided by true positives plus "
"false positives"
msgstr ""

#. type: example
#: damegender.texi:537
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(femalefemale + malemale ) /\n"
"(femalefemale + malemale + femalemale)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:540
msgid ""
"@strong{Recall} is about true positives divided by true positives plus false "
"negatives."
msgstr ""

#. type: example
#: damegender.texi:545
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(femalefemale + malemale ) /\n"
"(femalefemale + malemale + malefemale +\n"
"+ femaleundefined + maleundefined)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:548
msgid "@strong{Accuracy} is about true positives divided by all."
msgstr ""

#. type: example
#: damegender.texi:553
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(femalefemale + malemale ) /\n"
"(femalefemale + malemale + malefemale +\n"
"+ femalemale + femaleundefined + maleundefined)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: damegender.texi:557
msgid ""
"The @strong{F1 score} is the harmonic mean of precision and recall taking "
"both metrics into account in the following equation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: example
#: damegender.texi:562
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"2 * (\n"
"(precision * recall) /\n"
"(precision + recall))\n"
msgstr ""

